<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">
Distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Discobola" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Discobola" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Discobola</taxonomicName>
by more heavily marked wings and the structure of the male genitalia (Fig. 3), see also (
<bibRefCitation author="Stary, J." journalOrPublisher="Folia Facultatis Scientiarum Naturalium Universitatis Purkynianae Brunensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" pagination="13 - 22" title="Bemerkungen zu einigen wenig bekannten Limoniinen aus der Tschechoslowakei (Tipulidae, Diptera)" volume="15" year="1974">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Starý">Stary</normalizedToken>
1974
</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 5, 6).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">
Palaearctic (
<bibRefCitation pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">Oosterbroek 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Karelian record is the northernmost one. Closest locations are in Poland, Lithuania and the Republic of Bashkortostan in Russia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="22175">
Poorly known, though associations with dead wood and wood-destroying fungi were reported (
<bibRefCitation author="Sevcik, J." journalOrPublisher="Slezske Zemske Muzeum Opava" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" pagination="1 - 84" title="Diptera associated with fungi in the Czech and Slovak Republics" volume="55" year="2006">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ševčík">Sevcik</normalizedToken>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Wiedenska, J." editor="Bogdanowicz, W." journalOrPublisher="Muzeum i Instytut Zoologii PAN, Warszawa" pageId="0" pageNumber="22175" title="Fauna of Poland. Characteristics and checklist of species, Part 2" year="2007">Wiedenska 2007</bibRefCitation>
). This species was collected from a windthrown aspen, colonised by 15 species of macrofungi (Table 1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
